						               													<description>Nightshift is a thematic board game that immerses players into the role of a strip club dancer. The customer stories and gameplay are inspired by the creator&amp;rsquo;s personal experience working as a stripper, providing an authentic and empowering take on this often misunderstood profession.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players must select from five different dancers who each have a distinct approach to charming customers. The goal is to earn the most money over the night. Be careful about interfering with another dancer&amp;rsquo;s customer or your night may not run so smoothly...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players use action points to navigate the club and discover new customers. Each customer is unique and has variable wealth and loyalty, as well as a diverse range of potential outcomes. Choose your customers wisely! Engaging with a customer involves rolling the dice, which combined with the Player's abilities, power cards, and potentially a few drinks, will determine the outcome.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Successfully getting a customer to the Private Room, or even better, the VIP Room, initiates a theme-based &amp;quot;push-your-luck&amp;quot; challenge. The aim is to maximize earnings from the customer without breaking the illusion. This is achieved by performing a combination of dance moves (via card draws) in the Private Room or deepening your connection (via dice rolls) in the VIP Room, with the ultimate goal of making the customer fall in love.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players can purchase champagne from the bar, which serves as a valuable tool for persuading customers to extend their stay in the Private Room or VIP Room.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Throughout the game players must track when they are rostered on the stage, which provides an opportunity to collect additional tips and acquire power cards. These unique powers add another layer of strategy and player interaction to the gameplay, ensuring an engaging and immersive experience for all.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
